                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851D.001/45: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United, Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-28T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 28, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 28—4:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2925. Department’s 2395, April 15, 8 p.m. and Embassy’s 2909, April 27, midnight.
                    Strang has just telephoned us to say that Massigli has assured the Foreign
                    Office that instructions will be issued today recalling Bertaud to London. The
                    Foreign Office is telegraphing <pb facs="0290" n="278" xml:id="pg_278"/> the
                    Governor of Trinidad in this sense, instructing him to get in touch with Bertaud
                    and arrange for his early departure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
